Class ADisplay

java.lang.Object
me.gamercoder215.superadvancements.advancement.ADisplay
Direct Known Subclasses:
BukkitDisplay, PaperDisplay, SpigotDisplay
public abstract class ADisplay extends Object
Abstract Implementation of an Advancement's Display in the player's Advancement Menu.

    • setBackgroundTexture

      public void setBackgroundTexture(@Nullable @Nullable String texture)

      Sets the background texture of the Advancement. This will only apply to the root advancement.

      This should link to a file in one of the player's resource packs (or the Vanilla textures), such as:

      setBackgroundTexture("textures/block/stone.png")

      Parameters:
      texture - Texture String

    • setBackgroundTexture

      public void setBackgroundTexture(@Nullable @Nullable Material m)

      Sets the background texture of the Advancement. This will only apply to the root advancement.

      This sets the background texture to textures/block/<material>.png if Material.isBlock() returns true or textures/item/<material>.png if it returns false.

      Parameters:
      m - Material to use
